<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-10-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-10-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="223" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d223">
                        <head>No. 223.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Señor <persName type="to">Perez</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-10-07"><hi rend="italic">October</hi> 7,
                                1887</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 3d instant, saying that the Nicaraguan
                            Congress had rejected the treaty of July 26, 1887, for the adjustment of
                            the boundary difficulty between that Government and Costa Rica, and to
                            observe that I thus learn with regret that the expected course of direct
                            settlement of the questions between two countries to which the United
                            States are equally friendly is interrupted.</p>
                        <p>Accept sir, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>